text.section:
A managing general agent may not:
commit the insurer to participate in insurance or reinsurance syndicates;
appoint or hire an insurance producer to solicit, procure, or negotiate insurance contracts for the insurer without ensuring that the insurance producer is licensed under Title 10, Subtitle 1 of this article;
take an action that would violate § 27-503 of this article if taken directly by the insurer;
without the insurer's written approval, pay or commit the insurer to pay a claim, net of reinsurance, that exceeds 1% of the insurer's policyholder surplus as of December 31 of the immediately preceding calendar year;
without the insurer's prior written approval, collect any payment from a reinsurer;
commit the insurer to a claim settlement with a reinsurer;
employ an individual who also is employed by the insurer;
allow an agent or employee of the managing general agent to serve on the insurer's board of directors; or
appoint a submanaging general agent unless:
approval of the appointment is obtained from the Commissioner and from the insurer for whom the managing general agent acts; and
the submanaging general agent complies with any requirements imposed by the Commissioner under § 8-213 of this subtitle.
